Minecraft Version Manifest Downloader
=====================================

This is a simple shell script that downloads all Minecraft version JSON
files from Mojang's official version manifest.

It uses curl to download data and jq to parse JSON.

Requirements
------------

jq
curl

Both tools must be installed and available in PATH.

Usage
-----

Make the script executable:

    chmod +x script.sh

Run it:

    ./script.sh

Options
-------

    --skip-release     do not download release versions
    --skip-snapshot    do not download snapshot versions
    --skip-alpha       do not download old alpha versions
    --skip-beta        do not download old beta versions

Multiple options can be combined.

Output
------

All downloaded version files are saved under:

    results/

Each file is named:

    <version_id>.json

Failures
---------

If a download fails, the version id is written to:

    failed_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS.txt

If any failure occurs, the script exits with status 1.

Network
-------

The script downloads the version manifest from Mojang:

    https://piston-meta.mojang.com/mc/game/version_manifest_v2.json

It retries failed requests automatically (curl retry enabled).

Environment
-----------

You may override the manifest URL using:

    VERSION_MANIFEST_REMOTE

